      <hedline>
        <hl1>Alone at the Top</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Timothy Tung letter on Roger Lowenstein's August 27 article calls Sanford I Weill ruthless, manipulative and unsentimental (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Sanford I. Weill is alone at the top because he is ruthless, manipulative and unsentimental (Roger Lowenstein, Aug. 27). He gets the prize because, like Richard in ''Survivor,'' he believes it is all a game of strategy and alliances.</p>
        <p>Timothy Tung  New York</p>
      </block>
